.SH "NAME"
Dist::Zilla::PluginBundle::Filter \- use another bundle, with some plugins removed
.SH "VERSION"
.IX Header "VERSION"
version 6.017
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
In your \fIdist.ini\fR:
.PP
.Vb 6
\&  [@Filter]
\&  \-bundle = @Basic
\&  \-version = 5.031
\&  \-remove = ShareDir
\&  \-remove = UploadToCPAN
\&  option = for_basic
.Ve
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This plugin bundle actually wraps and modifies another plugin bundle.  It
includes all the configuration for the bundle named in the \f(CW\*(C`\-bundle\*(C'\fR attribute,
but removes all the entries whose package is given in the \f(CW\*(C`\-remove\*(C'\fR attributes.
.PP
A minimum required version of the bundle can be specified with the \f(CW\*(C`\-version\*(C'\fR 
attribute.
.PP
Options not prefixed with \f(CW\*(C`\-\*(C'\fR will be passed to the bundle to be filtered.
.PP
\&\fB\s-1NOTE:\s0\fR When you filter a bundle you \fB\s-1SHOULD NOT\s0\fR include it directly in
your \f(CW\*(C`dist.ini\*(C'\fR file. This plugin will take care of including it for you.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.IX Header "SEE ALSO"
Core Dist::Zilla plugins: \f(CW@Basic\fR.
.PP
